dvbRcsMib.name: dvbRcsMib

revisions.description: Revision of this MIB module, following MIB doctor review and adjustments based on the MIB authoring guidelines from the IETF.

dvbRcsMib.contactinfo: The SatLabs Group Web: www.satlabs.org E-mail: info@satlabs.org
dvbRcsMib.description: DVB-RCS MIB subtree. This MIB module applies to equipment that is a Return Channel Satellite Terminal (RCST), defined in the Digital Video Broadcasting Return Channel via Satellite system (DVB-RCS) standard (ETSI EN 301 790 Digital Video Broadcasting (DVB); Interaction Channel for Satellite Distribution Systems, European Telecommunications Standards Institute (ETSI)). It defines a set of MIB objects to characterize the behavior and performance of network-layer entities implementing DVB-RCS. This MIB module is intended to be used by DVB-RCS equipment following the SatLabs System Recommendations, defined by the SatLabs Group and available at www.satlabs.org. Note that, if not stated otherwise in the object DESCRIPTION clause, all writable objects are persistent. Copyright (C) The IETF Trust (2010). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC 5728; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

DvbRcsSatLabsProfileMap.name: DvbRcsSatLabsProfileMap
DvbRcsSatLabsProfileMap.description: This textual convention enumerates the declaration of the SatLabs-defined terminal profiles. The mapping to the profiles is to be understood as described here. (0) refers to the most significant bit. dvbs(0) -> DVBS profile (DVB-S support) dvbs2ccm(1) -> DVB-S2 CCM profile (CCM support) dvbs2acm(2) -> DVB-S2 ACM profile (CCM, VCM and ACM support)
DvbRcsSatLabsProfileMap.reference: SatLabs System Recommendations, available at www.satlabs.org.

DvbRcsSatLabsOptionMap.name: DvbRcsSatLabsOptionMap
DvbRcsSatLabsOptionMap.description: This textual convention enumerates the declaration of the SatLabs-defined options. A value of 1 indicates that the respective option is supported. The mapping to the options is to be understood as described here. (0) refers to the most significant bit. mpegTrf(0) -> MPEG_TRF coarseSync(1) -> COARSE_SYNC wideHop(2) -> WIDE_HOPP fastHop(3) -> FAST_HOPP dynamicMfTdma(4) -> Dynamic_MF_TDMA contentionSync(5) -> CONTENTION_SYNC qpskLow(6) -> QPSKLOW mod16Apsk(7) -> 16APSK mod32Apsk(8) -> 32APSK normalFec(9) -> NORMALFEC multiTs(10) -> MULTITS gsTs(11) -> GSTS enhQoS(12) -> ENHQOS pep(13) -> PEP http(14) -> HTTP ftp(15) -> FTP dns(16) -> DNS chIdStrict(17) -> CHID_STRICT nlid(18) -> NLID snmpMisc(19) -> SNMPMISC The support of specific options mandates the support of specific objects and access levels.
DvbRcsSatLabsOptionMap.reference: SatLabs System Recommendations, available at www.satlabs.org.

DvbRcsSatLabsFeatureMap.name: DvbRcsSatLabsFeatureMap
DvbRcsSatLabsFeatureMap.description: This textual convention enumerates the declaration of the SatLabs-specified compatibility and configuration features. A value of 1 indicates that the respective feature is supported. The mapping to the features is to be understood as described here. (0) refers to the most significant bit. rcstPara(0) -> RCST_PARA feature installLog(1) -> INSTALL_LOG feature enhClassifier(2) -> ENHCLASSIFIER feature routeId(3) -> ROUTE_ID feature oduList(4) -> ODULIST feature extNetwork(5) -> EXTNETWORK feature extControl(6) -> EXTCONTROL feature extConfig(7) -> EXTCONFIG feature extStatus(8) -> EXTSTATUS feature mpaf(9) -> MPAF feature The support of specific features mandates the support of specific objects and access levels.
DvbRcsSatLabsFeatureMap.reference: SatLabs System Recommendations, available at www.satlabs.org.

dvbRcsSystemMibRevision.name: dvbRcsSystemMibRevision
dvbRcsSystemMibRevision.description: This object allows the SNMP agent to report the implemented MIB module revision. The supported REVISION of this module is reported.

dvbRcsSystemSatLabsProfilesDeclaration.name: dvbRcsSystemSatLabsProfilesDeclaration
dvbRcsSystemSatLabsProfilesDeclaration.description: Indicates the SatLabs profiles supported, as defined in the SatLabs System Recommendations.

dvbRcsSystemSatLabsOptionsDeclaration.name: dvbRcsSystemSatLabsOptionsDeclaration
dvbRcsSystemSatLabsOptionsDeclaration.description: Indicates the SatLabs options supported, as defined in the SatLabs System Recommendations.

dvbRcsSystemSatLabsFeaturesDeclaration.name: dvbRcsSystemSatLabsFeaturesDeclaration
dvbRcsSystemSatLabsFeaturesDeclaration.description: Indicates the optional compatibility features and minor options supported, as defined in the SatLabs System Recommendations.

dvbRcsSystemLocation.name: dvbRcsSystemLocation
dvbRcsSystemLocation.description: Physical location of the ODU antenna expressed as longitude, latitude, and altitude. The string shall have 31 characters in the following format: <xxxx.xxx>,<a>,<yyyyy.yyy>,<b>,<zzzz.z>,M where x, y and z represents digits, a=N or S, b=E or W, Reading the digits from left to right: 'x' 7 latitude digits; x digits 1-2 contain the degrees, x digits 3-7 contain the minutes in decimal; 'y' 8 longitude digits; y digits 1-3 contain the degrees, y digits 4-8 contain the minutes in decimal; 'z' 5 altitude digits; meters above sea level in decimal; '.' is the decimal point; ',' is the field separator; 'M' is the indicator for altitude meters. This format is a modified subset of the NMEA 0183 (National Marine Electronics Association, Interface Standard) format for Global Positioning System Fix Data. This location and the satellite position are used to calculate the RCST-satellite path delay. Note: The system.sysLocation object of MIB-II provides physical location of the IDU unit.

dvbRcsSystemOduAntennaGain.name: dvbRcsSystemOduAntennaGain
dvbRcsSystemOduAntennaGain.description: Antenna peak gain of the ODU.

dvbRcsSystemOduSspa.name: dvbRcsSystemOduSspa
dvbRcsSystemOduSspa.description: Power level of the Solid State Power Amplifier installed in the ODU.

dvbRcsSystemOduTxType.name: dvbRcsSystemOduTxType
dvbRcsSystemOduTxType.description: Type of transmitter installed in the ODU.

dvbRcsSystemOduRxType.name: dvbRcsSystemOduRxType
dvbRcsSystemOduRxType.description: Type of LNB installed in the ODU, with information such as vendor type, output type (single, twin, quad,...), etc.

dvbRcsSystemOduRxBand.name: dvbRcsSystemOduRxBand
dvbRcsSystemOduRxBand.description: LNB High Band / Low Band selector. High Band corresponds to the emission of an 18-26 kHz tone with 0.4-0.8 Vpp in the Rx IFL cable: (0) - High Band (1) - Low Band

dvbRcsSystemOduRxLO.name: dvbRcsSystemOduRxLO
dvbRcsSystemOduRxLO.description: Frequency of LNB Local Oscillator (in 100 Hz)

dvbRcsSystemOduTxLO.name: dvbRcsSystemOduTxLO
dvbRcsSystemOduTxLO.description: Frequency of Block Up-Converter Local Oscillator (in 100 Hz).

dvbRcsTcpPep.name: dvbRcsTcpPep
dvbRcsTcpPep.description: Status and control of embedded TCP PEP. 0 - disabled or not implemented 1 - enabled

dvbRcsHttpPep.name: dvbRcsHttpPep
dvbRcsHttpPep.description: Status and control of embedded HTTP PEP. 0 - disabled or not implemented 1 - enabled

dvbRcsOduTxTypeTable.name: dvbRcsOduTxTypeTable
dvbRcsOduTxTypeTable.description: This table contains the identification of each well- known BUC type supported by the IDU and provides its associated index.

dvbRcsOduTxTypeEntry.name: dvbRcsOduTxTypeEntry
dvbRcsOduTxTypeEntry.description: An entry in the BUC type table.

dvbRcsOduTxTypeDescription.name: dvbRcsOduTxTypeDescription
dvbRcsOduTxTypeDescription.description: Text-based identification of a BUC type.

dvbRcsOduTxType.name: dvbRcsOduTxType
dvbRcsOduTxType.description: Index of the selected BUC type.

dvbRcsOduRxTypeTable.name: dvbRcsOduRxTypeTable
dvbRcsOduRxTypeTable.description: This table contains the identification of each well- known LNB type supported by the IDU and provides its associated index.

dvbRcsOduRxTypeEntry.name: dvbRcsOduRxTypeEntry
dvbRcsOduRxTypeEntry.description: An entry in the LNB type table.

dvbRcsOduRxTypeDescription.name: dvbRcsOduRxTypeDescription
dvbRcsOduRxTypeDescription.description: Text-based identification of an LNB type.

dvbRcsOduRxType.name: dvbRcsOduRxType
dvbRcsOduRxType.description: Index of the selected LNB type.

dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeTable.name: dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeTable
dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeTable.description: This table contains the identification of each well- known antenna type supported by the IDU and provides its associated index.

dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeEntry.name: dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeEntry
dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeEntry.description: An entry in the antenna type table.

dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeDescription.name: dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeDescription
dvbRcsOduAntennaTypeDescription.description: Text-based identification of an antenna type.

dvbRcsOduAntennaType.name: dvbRcsOduAntennaType
dvbRcsOduAntennaType.description: Index of the selected antenna type.

dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressType.name: dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressType
dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address of dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddress. If the terminal OAM Internet address is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddress.name: dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddress
dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddress.description: OAM IP Address of the RCST. This object is used with both IP and interfaces MIB-II subgroups. It uniquely determines the interface through which OAM traffic passes. The OAM IP address may be statically or dynamically assigned. It is system dependent whether the OAM IP address and the Traffic IP address are the same address. If the terminal has no OAM Internet address assigned or if this Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length OCTET STRING. The InetAddressType is given by the dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressType object.

dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressPrefixLength.name: dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressPrefixLength
dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressPrefixLength.description: Prefix length for the OAM IP Address. If this address prefix is unknown or does not apply, the value is zero.

dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressAssign.name: dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressAssign
dvbRcsNetworkOamInetAddressAssign.description: Identifies whether the OAM IP address is statically (1) or dynamically (2) assigned.

dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddressType.name: dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddressType
dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address of dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddress. If the terminal Internet address on the LAN interface is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddress.name: dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddress
dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddress.description: IP address of the LAN interface of the terminal. If the terminal has no Internet address assigned on the LAN interface or if this Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length OCTET STRING. The InetAddressType is given by the dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddressType object.

dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddressPrefixLength.name: dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddressPrefixLength
dvbRcsNetworkLanInetAddressPrefixLength.description: Prefix length for the LAN IP Address of the terminal. If this address prefix is unknown or does not apply, the value is zero.

dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayI.name: dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayInetAddressType
dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayI.description: The type of Internet address of dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayInetAddress. If the default gateway Internet address is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayI.name: dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayInetAddress
dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayI.description: IP address of the default gateway for the air interface. If the terminal has no default gateway assigned on the air interface or if this Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length OCTET STRING. The InetAddressType is given by the dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayInetAddressType object.

dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayI.name: dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayInetAddressPrefixLength
dvbRcsNetworkAirInterfaceDefaultGatewayI.description: Prefix length for the IP address of the default gateway for the air interface. If this address prefix is unknown or does not apply, the value is zero.

dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddressType.name: dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddressType
dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address of dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddress. If the primary DNS server Internet address is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddress.name: dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddress
dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddress.description: IP address of the primary DNS server in the NCC. If the terminal has no primary DNS server assigned or if this Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length OCTET STRING. The InetAddressType is given by the dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddressType object.

dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddressPrefixL.name: dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddressPrefixLength
dvbRcsPrimaryDnsServerInetAddressPrefixL.description: Prefix length for the IP address of the primary DNS server in the NCC. If this address prefix is unknown or does not apply, the value is zero.

dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddressType.name: dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddressType
dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address of dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddress. If the secondary DNS server Internet address is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddress.name: dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddress
dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddress.description: IP address of the secondary DNS server in the NCC. If the terminal has no secondary DNS server assigned or if this Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length OCTET STRING. The InetAddressType is given by the dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddressType object.

dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddressPrefi.name: dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddressPrefixLength
dvbRcsSecondaryDnsServerInetAddressPrefi.description: Prefix length for the IP address of the secondary DNS server in the NCC. If this address prefix is unknown or does not apply, the value is zero.

dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddressType.name: dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddressType
dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address of dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddress. If the management server Internet address is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddress.name: dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddress
dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddress.description: IP address of the management server in the NCC. If the terminal has no management server assigned or if this Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length OCTET STRING. The InetAddressType is given by the dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddressType object.

dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddressPrefixLeng.name: dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddressPrefixLength
dvbRcsNetworkNccMgtInetAddressPrefixLeng.description: Prefix length for the IP address of the management server in the NCC. If this address prefix is unknown or does not apply, the value is zero.

dvbRcsNetworkConfigFileDownloadUrl.name: dvbRcsNetworkConfigFileDownloadUrl
dvbRcsNetworkConfigFileDownloadUrl.description: Full path name for the configuration file download. It includes the protocol type (TFTP or FTP) and the associated server IP address or hostname. Hostname can only be used if DNS is supported by the RCST. The format of this parameter follows RFC 3986.

dvbRcsNetworkInstallLogFileDownloadUrl.name: dvbRcsNetworkInstallLogFileDownloadUrl
dvbRcsNetworkInstallLogFileDownloadUrl.description: Full path of the installation log file to download. It includes the protocol type (TFTP or FTP) and the associated server IP address or hostname. Hostname can only be used if DNS is supported by the RCST. The installation log file can be created on the installer's computer and downloaded to the RCST. The format of this parameter follows RFC 3986.

dvbRcsNetworkConfigFileUploadUrl.name: dvbRcsNetworkConfigFileUploadUrl
dvbRcsNetworkConfigFileUploadUrl.description: Full path name for the configuration file upload. It includes the protocol type (TFTP or FTP) and the associated server IP address or hostname. Hostname can only be used if DNS is supported by the RCST. The format of this parameter follows RFC 3986.

dvbRcsNetworkLogFileUploadUrl.name: dvbRcsNetworkLogFileUploadUrl
dvbRcsNetworkLogFileUploadUrl.description: Full path of the event log file. It includes the protocol type (TFTP or FTP) and the associated server IP address or hostname. Hostname can only be used if DNS is supported by the RCST. The format of this parameter follows RFC 3986.

dvbRcsNetworkInstallLogFileUploadUrl.name: dvbRcsNetworkInstallLogFileUploadUrl
dvbRcsNetworkInstallLogFileUploadUrl.description: Full path of the installation log file. It includes the protocol type (TFTP or FTP) and the associated server IP address or hostname. Hostname can only be used if DNS is supported by the RCST. The installation log file can be retrieved from the RCST by the NCC or by the installer via the LAN. The format of this parameter follows RFC 3986.

dvbRcsInstallAntennaAlignmentState.name: dvbRcsInstallAntennaAlignmentState
dvbRcsInstallAntennaAlignmentState.description: Indicates the alignment state of the antenna: (1)-Start; (2)-Deny; (3)-Continue; (4)-Stop; (5)-Success; (6)-Fail

dvbRcsInstallCwFrequency.name: dvbRcsInstallCwFrequency
dvbRcsInstallCwFrequency.description: Frequency of the transmitted Continuous Wave carrier (in 100 Hz). Minimum required precision is 1 kHz.

dvbRcsInstallCwMaxDuration.name: dvbRcsInstallCwMaxDuration
dvbRcsInstallCwMaxDuration.description: Time after which the Continuous Wave carrier must be put down (in seconds).

dvbRcsInstallCwPower.name: dvbRcsInstallCwPower
dvbRcsInstallCwPower.description: IDU TX output level when the IDU is configured to send CW. The resolution is 0.1 dBm and the accuracy is +/- 1 dBm. Reconfiguration is applied immediately to a CW.

dvbRcsInstallCoPolReading.name: dvbRcsInstallCoPolReading
dvbRcsInstallCoPolReading.description: Co-polarization measured value during installation procedure (in 0.1 dB).

dvbRcsInstallXPolReading.name: dvbRcsInstallXPolReading
dvbRcsInstallXPolReading.description: Cross-polarization measured value during installation procedure (in 0.1 dB).

dvbRcsInstallCoPolTarget.name: dvbRcsInstallCoPolTarget
dvbRcsInstallCoPolTarget.description: Co-polarization target value during installation procedure (in 0.1 dB).

dvbRcsInstallXPolTarget.name: dvbRcsInstallXPolTarget
dvbRcsInstallXPolTarget.description: Cross-polarization target value during installation procedure (in 0.1 dB).

dvbRcsInstallStandByDuration.name: dvbRcsInstallStandByDuration
dvbRcsInstallStandByDuration.description: Time to wait in stand-by mode (in seconds).

dvbRcsInstallTargetEsN0.name: dvbRcsInstallTargetEsN0
dvbRcsInstallTargetEsN0.description: This value describes the wanted Es/N0 value that enables operation of the return link with the required error performance. The values shall be given in tenth of dB and the initial value shall be equal to 7 dB. The range shall be from 0 dB to 31.5 dB, with a precision of 0.1 dB.

dvbRcsPktClassTable.name: dvbRcsPktClassTable
dvbRcsPktClassTable.description: This table describes the packet classification used in the DVB-RCS terminal. The number of entries is specified by dvbRcsPktClassIndex.

dvbRcsPktClassEntry.name: dvbRcsPktClassEntry
dvbRcsPktClassEntry.description: An entry in the packet classification table. One object type of each entry may have a value in the active range (a non-default value). The other object types are then assumed to be set to 'inactive'. The entry with the lowest index value takes precedence when classifying a packet.

dvbRcsPktClassIndex.name: dvbRcsPktClassIndex
dvbRcsPktClassIndex.description: Index automatically incremented by one at row creation.

dvbRcsPktClassDscpLow.name: dvbRcsPktClassDscpLow
dvbRcsPktClassDscpLow.description: This object specifies the low value of a range of Diffserv Code Point (DSCP) values to which a packet is compared.

dvbRcsPktClassDscpHigh.name: dvbRcsPktClassDscpHigh
dvbRcsPktClassDscpHigh.description: This object specifies the high value of a range of Diffserv Code Point (DSCP) values to which a packet is compared.

dvbRcsPktClassDscpMarkValue.name: dvbRcsPktClassDscpMarkValue
dvbRcsPktClassDscpMarkValue.description: This object is the Diffserv Code Point (DSCP) value used to mark the packet; -1 indicates no DSCP marking. Possible DSCP marks values are (0..63)

dvbRcsPktClassIpProtocol.name: dvbRcsPktClassIpProtocol
dvbRcsPktClassIpProtocol.description: This object specifies the IP protocol to which a packet is compared. A value of 255 means match all.

dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddressType.name: dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddressType
dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address of dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddress. If the packet class source Internet address is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddress.name: dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddress
dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddress.description: This object specifies the IP source address to which a packet is compared. If the packet class has no source Internet address assigned or if this Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length OCTET STRING. The InetAddressType is given by the dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddressType object.

dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddressPrefixLength.name: dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddressPrefixLength
dvbRcsPktClassSrcInetAddressPrefixLength.description: Prefix length of the IP source address that will be matched for this packet class. A value of zero indicates that the selectivity is inactive.

dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddressType.name: dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddressType
dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddressType.description: The type of Internet address of dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddress. If the packet class destination Internet address is unassigned or unknown, then the value of this object is unknown(0).

dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddress.name: dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddress
dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddress.description: This object specifies the IP destination address to which a packet is compared. If the packet class has no destination Internet address assigned or if this Internet address is unknown, the value of this object is the zero-length OCTET STRING. The InetAddressType is given by the dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddressType object.

dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddressPrefixLength.name: dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddressPrefixLength
dvbRcsPktClassDstInetAddressPrefixLength.description: Prefix length of the IP source address that will be matched for this packet class. A value of zero indicates that the selectivity is inactive.

dvbRcsPktClassSrcPortLow.name: dvbRcsPktClassSrcPortLow
dvbRcsPktClassSrcPortLow.description: This object specifies the low range of the source port to which a packet is compared. A value of 0 indicates that the selectivity is inactive.

dvbRcsPktClassSrcPortHigh.name: dvbRcsPktClassSrcPortHigh
dvbRcsPktClassSrcPortHigh.description: This object specifies the high range of the source port to which a packet is compared. A value of 0 indicates that the selectivity is inactive.

dvbRcsPktClassDstPortLow.name: dvbRcsPktClassDstPortLow
dvbRcsPktClassDstPortLow.description: This object specifies the low range of the destination port to which a packet is compared. A value of 0 indicates that the selectivity is inactive.

dvbRcsPktClassDstPortHigh.name: dvbRcsPktClassDstPortHigh
dvbRcsPktClassDstPortHigh.description: This object specifies the high range of the destination port to which a packet is compared. A value of 0 indicates that the selectivity is inactive.

dvbRcsPktClassVlanUserPri.name: dvbRcsPktClassVlanUserPri
dvbRcsPktClassVlanUserPri.description: This object specifies the VLAN User Priority to which a packet is compared. A value of -1 indicates that the selectivity is inactive.

dvbRcsPktClassPhbAssociation.name: dvbRcsPktClassPhbAssociation
dvbRcsPktClassPhbAssociation.description: Associate the filter entry to a specific PHB (refer to dvbRcsPhbIdentifier).

dvbRcsPktClassRowStatus.name: dvbRcsPktClassRowStatus
dvbRcsPktClassRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. All writable objects in this row may be modified at any time.

dvbRcsPhbMappingTable.name: dvbRcsPhbMappingTable
dvbRcsPhbMappingTable.description: This table is a list of Per-Hop Behavior (PHB) MIB entries. It describes the PHB mapping to the Request Class.

dvbRcsPhbMappingEntry.name: dvbRcsPhbMappingEntry
dvbRcsPhbMappingEntry.description: An entry in the PHB mapping table.

dvbRcsPhbIdentifier.name: dvbRcsPhbIdentifier
dvbRcsPhbIdentifier.description: Identification of the Per-Hop Behavior (PHB). It follows the unsigned 16-bit binary encoding as specified in RFC 3140. The value 0 designates the Default PHB.

dvbRcsPhbName.name: dvbRcsPhbName
dvbRcsPhbName.description: The name of the Per-Hop Behavior (PHB).

dvbRcsPhbRequestClassAssociation.name: dvbRcsPhbRequestClassAssociation
dvbRcsPhbRequestClassAssociation.description: This object is an association of this Per-Hop Behavior (PHB) to a Request Class (by reference to a Request Class index).

dvbRcsPhbMappingRowStatus.name: dvbRcsPhbMappingRowStatus
dvbRcsPhbMappingRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. All writable objects in this row may be modified at any time.

dvbRcsRequestClassTable.name: dvbRcsRequestClassTable
dvbRcsRequestClassTable.description: This table is a list of Request Class entries. This class describes the layer 2 QoS objects.

dvbRcsRequestClassEntry.name: dvbRcsRequestClassEntry
dvbRcsRequestClassEntry.description: An entry in the Request Class table.

dvbRcsRequestClassIndex.name: dvbRcsRequestClassIndex
dvbRcsRequestClassIndex.description: Index of the Request Class table. A total of 16 entries are supported.

dvbRcsRequestClassChanId.name: dvbRcsRequestClassChanId
dvbRcsRequestClassChanId.description: Channel ID of the Request Class.

dvbRcsRequestClassVccVpi.name: dvbRcsRequestClassVccVpi
dvbRcsRequestClassVccVpi.description: Defines the VPI used for the Request Class (ATM profile).

dvbRcsRequestClassVccVci.name: dvbRcsRequestClassVccVci
dvbRcsRequestClassVccVci.description: Defines the VCI used for the Request Class (ATM profile).

dvbRcsRequestClassPidPoolReference.name: dvbRcsRequestClassPidPoolReference
dvbRcsRequestClassPidPoolReference.description: Reference to the Packet IDentifier (PID) pool applicable for the Request Class.

dvbRcsRequestClassCra.name: dvbRcsRequestClassCra
dvbRcsRequestClassCra.description: Defines the Continuous Rate Assignment (CRA) level for the Request Class in bits per second (bit/s).

dvbRcsRequestClassRbdcMax.name: dvbRcsRequestClassRbdcMax
dvbRcsRequestClassRbdcMax.description: Maximum Rate-Based Dynamic Capacity (RBDC) that can be requested for the Request Class, in number of 2 kbit/s.

dvbRcsRequestClassRbdcTimeout.name: dvbRcsRequestClassRbdcTimeout
dvbRcsRequestClassRbdcTimeout.description: Persistence of the Rate-Based Dynamic Capacity (RBDC) request, expressed in superframes.

dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcMax.name: dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcMax
dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcMax.description: Maximum Volume-Based Dynamic Capacity (VBDC) that can be allocated to the Request Class, in payload units (one ATM cell or one MPEG packet) per superframe.

dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcTimeout.name: dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcTimeout
dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcTimeout.description: Time after which the RCST considers that the pending requests are lost. The RCST may issue new requests for that traffic. Volume-Based Dynamic Capacity (VBDC) Timeout is expressed in superframes.

dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcMaxBackLog.name: dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcMaxBackLog
dvbRcsRequestClassVbdcMaxBackLog.description: Volume-Based Dynamic Capacity (VBDC) back log per Request Class (expressed in bytes).

dvbRcsRequestClassRowStatus.name: dvbRcsRequestClassRowStatus
dvbRcsRequestClassRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. It is not possible to change values in a row of this table while the row is active.

dvbRcsPidPoolTable.name: dvbRcsPidPoolTable
dvbRcsPidPoolTable.description: This table contains the Packet IDentifier (PID) pools. For the MPEG profile, several Request Classes may be mapped within a pool of several PIDs to allow Section Packing across several Request Classes. A PID value may occur in more than one PID pool. Each PID value can effectively occur only once in each pool.

dvbRcsPidPoolEntry.name: dvbRcsPidPoolEntry
dvbRcsPidPoolEntry.description: An entry in the PID pool table.

dvbRcsPidPoolIndex.name: dvbRcsPidPoolIndex
dvbRcsPidPoolIndex.description: Index of the PID pool in the PID pool table.

dvbRcsPidIndex.name: dvbRcsPidIndex
dvbRcsPidIndex.description: Index of the PID entry within the PID pool.

dvbRcsPidValue.name: dvbRcsPidValue
dvbRcsPidValue.description: Defines one of the PIDs to be used in a PID pool of dvbRcsPidPoolIndex. A PID value may occur in more than one PID pool. Each PID value can effectively occur only once in each pool.

dvbRcsPidPoolRowStatus.name: dvbRcsPidPoolRowStatus
dvbRcsPidPoolRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. All writable objects in this row may be modified at any time.

dvbRcsQosGlobalRbdcMax.name: dvbRcsQosGlobalRbdcMax
dvbRcsQosGlobalRbdcMax.description: Global maximum RBDC that can be requested for the RCST, in number of 2 kbit/s.

dvbRcsQosGlobalVbdcMax.name: dvbRcsQosGlobalVbdcMax
dvbRcsQosGlobalVbdcMax.description: Global maximum VBDC that can be allocated to the RCST, in payload units (one ATM cell or one MPEG packet) per superframe.

dvbRcsQosGlobalVbdcMaxBackLog.name: dvbRcsQosGlobalVbdcMaxBackLog
dvbRcsQosGlobalVbdcMaxBackLog.description: Global VBDC back log at the RCST level (expressed in bytes). It is used only if the VBDC back log is not configured in the Request Class (expressed in bytes).

dvbRcsQosChannelIdStrictDispatching.name: dvbRcsQosChannelIdStrictDispatching
dvbRcsQosChannelIdStrictDispatching.description: Indicates whether the RCST will strictly follow RC association when signaled through Channel_ID in the TBTP: (0)- no strict association (1)- strict association

dvbRcsCtrlRebootCommand.name: dvbRcsCtrlRebootCommand
dvbRcsCtrlRebootCommand.description: This variable shall force the RCST to reboot: (1)- idle (2)- normal reboot (from current software load) (3)- reboot from alternate load (swap to alternate load before reboot)

dvbRcsCtrlRcstTxDisable.name: dvbRcsCtrlRcstTxDisable
dvbRcsCtrlRcstTxDisable.description: This variable shall force the RCST to stop transmission (transmit disabled as defined in SatLabs System Recommendations): (1)- idle (2)- initiate Tx Disabled

dvbRcsCtrlUserTrafficDisable.name: dvbRcsCtrlUserTrafficDisable
dvbRcsCtrlUserTrafficDisable.description: This variable shall disable user traffic (only RCST management traffic can be transmitted): (1)- idle (2)- disable user traffic

dvbRcsCtrlCwEnable.name: dvbRcsCtrlCwEnable
dvbRcsCtrlCwEnable.description: This variable will force the RCST to start transmission of CW, if the RCST is first set to the installation state and is properly configured for CW transmission: (1)- off (2)- on

dvbRcsCtrlOduTxReferenceEnable.name: dvbRcsCtrlOduTxReferenceEnable
dvbRcsCtrlOduTxReferenceEnable.description: Enables activation and deactivation of the 10 MHz reference clock in the Tx IFL cable: (1) off (2) on

dvbRcsCtrlOduTxDCEnable.name: dvbRcsCtrlOduTxDCEnable
dvbRcsCtrlOduTxDCEnable.description: Enables activation and deactivation of DC in the Tx IFL cable: (1) off (2) on

dvbRcsCtrlOduRxDCEnable.name: dvbRcsCtrlOduRxDCEnable
dvbRcsCtrlOduRxDCEnable.description: Enables activation and deactivation of DC in the Rx IFL cable: (1) off (2) on

dvbRcsCtrlDownloadFileCommand.name: dvbRcsCtrlDownloadFileCommand
dvbRcsCtrlDownloadFileCommand.description: This variable will initiate an RCST configuration file download process: (1) idle (2) download RCST configuration file from TFTP/FTP server (3) download RCST installation log file from TFTP/FTP server (INSTALL_LOG feature)

dvbRcsCtrlUploadFileCommand.name: dvbRcsCtrlUploadFileCommand
dvbRcsCtrlUploadFileCommand.description: This variable will initiate an RCST upload process: (1) idle (2) upload RCST configuration file to TFTP/FTP server (3) upload RCST event/alarm log file to TFTP/FTP server (4) upload RCST installation log file to TFTP/FTP server (INSTALL_LOG feature)

dvbRcsCtrlActivateConfigFileCommand.name: dvbRcsCtrlActivateConfigFileCommand
dvbRcsCtrlActivateConfigFileCommand.description: Triggers the RCST to use the configuration file and update its parameters accordingly. Some RCST implementations may require a reboot for the parameters to take effect (vendor specific). (1) idle (2) activate

dvbRcsCtrlRcstLogonCommand.name: dvbRcsCtrlRcstLogonCommand
dvbRcsCtrlRcstLogonCommand.description: This variable will initiate an RCST logon: (1) idle (2) initiate RCST logon

dvbRcsCtrlRcstLogoffCommand.name: dvbRcsCtrlRcstLogoffCommand
dvbRcsCtrlRcstLogoffCommand.description: This variable will initiate an RCST logoff: (1) idle (2) initiate RCST logoff

dvbRcsCtrlRcstRxReacquire.name: dvbRcsCtrlRcstRxReacquire
dvbRcsCtrlRcstRxReacquire.description: This variable will force the RCST to acquire the forward link and start receiving: (1) idle (2) reacquire forward link

dvbRcsRcstMode.name: dvbRcsRcstMode
dvbRcsRcstMode.description: Identifies the current mode of the RCST and allows the RCST to return to the installation mode when needed. Values for the RCST mode are: Installation (0) Operational (1)

dvbRcsRcstFaultStatus.name: dvbRcsRcstFaultStatus
dvbRcsRcstFaultStatus.description: Provides the fault status of the terminal. The fault status management is vendor specific. Values for the fault status are: no fault (0) fault (1)

dvbRcsRcstFwdLinkStatus.name: dvbRcsRcstFwdLinkStatus
dvbRcsRcstFwdLinkStatus.description: Provides the status of the RCST forward link. Values for the forward link status are: Not acquired (0) Acquired (1)

dvbRcsRcstRtnLinkStatus.name: dvbRcsRcstRtnLinkStatus
dvbRcsRcstRtnLinkStatus.description: Provides the status of the RCST return link. Values for the return link status are: Logged-off (0) Logged-on (1)

dvbRcsRcstLogUpdated.name: dvbRcsRcstLogUpdated
dvbRcsRcstLogUpdated.description: Indicates the existence of an updated event log file: No update (0) Event Log file updated (1) The RCST should remove the 'Event Log file updated' indication as the log file is fetched by the NCC.

dvbRcsRcstActivatedConfigFileVersion.name: dvbRcsRcstActivatedConfigFileVersion
dvbRcsRcstActivatedConfigFileVersion.description: Version of the most recently activated configuration file. The version is vendor specific.

dvbRcsRcstDownloadedConfigFileVersion.name: dvbRcsRcstDownloadedConfigFileVersion
dvbRcsRcstDownloadedConfigFileVersion.description: Version of the most recently downloaded configuration file. Version is vendor specific. If the value is different from dvbRcsRcstActivatedConfigFileVersion, it is pending for activation.

dvbRcsFwdStartTable.name: dvbRcsFwdStartTable
dvbRcsFwdStartTable.description: Lists forward link attachment points (e.g., different for installation and operation). The table describes the forward link parameters used for the start-up stream with the NCC.

dvbRcsFwdStartEntry.name: dvbRcsFwdStartEntry
dvbRcsFwdStartEntry.description: An entry in the Forward Link Start Configuration table.

dvbRcsFwdStartIndex.name: dvbRcsFwdStartIndex
dvbRcsFwdStartIndex.description: Index of the Forward Link StartConfig table.

dvbRcsFwdStartPopId.name: dvbRcsFwdStartPopId
dvbRcsFwdStartPopId.description: Population identifier associated with the start-up forward link: -1: any (auto) 0-65535: specific StartPopId If 'any' is set, the RCST will assume membership of any announced population ID and will commence with logon in accordance with this assumption.

dvbRcsFwdStartFrequency.name: dvbRcsFwdStartFrequency
dvbRcsFwdStartFrequency.description: Frequency of the start transponder carrying a Network Information Table to which any RCST shall trigger to acquire forward link. Its value shall be given in multiples of 100 kHz.

dvbRcsFwdStartPolar.name: dvbRcsFwdStartPolar
dvbRcsFwdStartPolar.description: 2-bit field giving the polarization of the start transponder carrying a Network Information Table to which any RCST shall trigger to acquire forward link: 00: linear and horizontal 01: linear and vertical 10: circular left 11: circular right

dvbRcsFwdStartFormat.name: dvbRcsFwdStartFormat
dvbRcsFwdStartFormat.description: Specifies the transmission format standard applied for the startup stream. The start transport stream carries a Network Information Table that the RCST uses for acquiring the forward link signaling. Supported values are: -1: unspecified (automatic format acquisition is assumed) 0: DVB-S (support of this value is mandatory if DVB-S support is claimed) 1: DVB-S2 with CCM (support of this value is mandatory if DVB-S2 CCM support is claimed) 2: DVB-S2 with VCM or ACM (support of this value is mandatory if DVB-S2 ACM support is claimed) This allows the RCST to discriminate between CCM and VCM/ACM when selecting the forward link. The support of automatic format selection is optional. One or several of the other format selections must be supported, according to the claimed SatLabs profile support.

dvbRcsFwdStartRolloff.name: dvbRcsFwdStartRolloff
dvbRcsFwdStartRolloff.description: Specifies the receive filter roll-off applied on the start transponder. The start transponder carries a Network Information Table that the RCST uses for acquiring the forward link signaling. Supported values are: 0: any (auto) 1: 0.20 2: 0.25 3: 0.35

dvbRcsFwdStartSymbolRate.name: dvbRcsFwdStartSymbolRate
dvbRcsFwdStartSymbolRate.description: Specifies the symbol rate on the start transponder carrying a Network Information Table to which any RCST shall trigger to acquire forward link. Its value shall be given in multiples of 100 symbols/s.

dvbRcsFwdStartInnerFec.name: dvbRcsFwdStartInnerFec
dvbRcsFwdStartInnerFec.description: Specifies the inner Forward Error Correction used on the start transponder carrying a Network Information Table to which any RCST shall trigger to acquire forward link. Supported values are: autoFec (-1), fecRate1/2 (0), fecRate2/3 (1), fecRate3/4 (2), fecRate5/6 (3), fecRate7/8 (4), fecRate8/9 (5), fecRate3/5 (6), fecRate4/5 (7), fecRate9/10 (8), fecRate2/5 (9), fecRate1/3 (10), fecRate1/4 (11), noInnerCode (12) The support of autoFec is optional.

dvbRcsFwdStartRowStatus.name: dvbRcsFwdStartRowStatus
dvbRcsFwdStartRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. It is not possible to change values in a row of this table while the row is active.

dvbRcsFwdStatusPopId.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusPopId
dvbRcsFwdStatusPopId.description: Population identifier applied at log-on: 0-65535: specific StartPopId If the RCST was allowed to logon with any population, the RCST will report the base number of the announced population ID indicated by the RCS Map Table linkage descriptor used at logon.

dvbRcsFwdStatusTable.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusTable
dvbRcsFwdStatusTable.description: This table describes the current status of Forward Link interfaces.

dvbRcsFwdStatusEntry.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusEntry
dvbRcsFwdStatusEntry.description: An entry in the forward link status table. Each entry is associated with a physical interface. An RCST shall support at least one entry.

dvbRcsFwdStatusIndex.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusIndex
dvbRcsFwdStatusIndex.description: Index of the forward link status table.

dvbRcsFwdStatusIfReference.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusIfReference
dvbRcsFwdStatusIfReference.description: Cross reference to the interface table.

dvbRcsFwdStatusNetId.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusNetId
dvbRcsFwdStatusNetId.description: Interactive network identifier of the forward link (from the RCS Map Table).

dvbRcsFwdStatusNetName.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusNetName
dvbRcsFwdStatusNetName.description: The name of the interactive network of the forward link (from the RCS Map Table).

dvbRcsFwdStatusFormat.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusFormat
dvbRcsFwdStatusFormat.description: Specifies the transmission format applied on the forward link. Supported values are (from RCS Map Table): 0: DVB-S 1: DVB-S2 using CCM 2: DVB-S2 using VCM or ACM 3: reserved

dvbRcsFwdStatusFrequency.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusFrequency
dvbRcsFwdStatusFrequency.description: An estimate of the frequency of the forward link. Its value shall be given in multiples of 100 kHz.

dvbRcsFwdStatusPolar.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusPolar
dvbRcsFwdStatusPolar.description: 2-bit field giving the polarization of the forward link Supported values are (from RCS Map Table): 00: linear and horizontal 01: linear and vertical 10: circular left 11: circular right

dvbRcsFwdStatusInnerFec.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusInnerFec
dvbRcsFwdStatusInnerFec.description: Specifies the inner Forward Error Correction used on the forward link for transmission to the RCST. Supported values are: unknown (-1), fecRate1/2 (0), fecRate2/3 (1), fecRate3/4 (2), fecRate5/6 (3), fecRate7/8 (4), fecRate8/9 (5), fecRate3/5 (6), fecRate4/5 (7), fecRate9/10 (8), fecRate2/5 (9), fecRate1/3 (10), fecRate1/4 (11), noInnerCode (12) The RCST will report a value that has been used for transmission to the RCST within the most recent 60 seconds. If this is not relevant, the RCST will report 'unknown'.

dvbRcsFwdStatusSymbolRate.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusSymbolRate
dvbRcsFwdStatusSymbolRate.description: An estimate of the symbol rate of the forward link. Its value shall be given in multiples of 100 symbols/s.

dvbRcsFwdStatusRolloff.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusRolloff
dvbRcsFwdStatusRolloff.description: An estimate of the roll-off applied on the forward link. Supported values are: 0: undefined 1: 0.20 2: 0.25 3: 0.35

dvbRcsFwdStatusModulation.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusModulation
dvbRcsFwdStatusModulation.description: Indicates the modulation on the forward link used for transmission to the RCST. Supported values are: 0: unknown 1: BPSK 2: QPSK 3: 8PSK 4: 16APSK 5: 32APSK The RCST will report a value that has been used for transmission to the RCST within the most recent 60 seconds. If this is not relevant, the RCST will report 'unknown'.

dvbRcsFwdStatusFecFrame.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusFecFrame
dvbRcsFwdStatusFecFrame.description: Indicates the frame length used on the forward link for transmission to the RCST. Supported values are: 0: Unknown 1: Short frame 2: Normal frame The RCST will report a value that has been used for transmission to the RCST within the most recent 60 seconds. If this is not relevant, the RCST will report 'unknown'.

dvbRcsFwdStatusPilot.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusPilot
dvbRcsFwdStatusPilot.description: Indicates whether pilots are used on the forward link for transmission to the RCST. Supported values are: 0: Unknown 1: Pilots are not used 2: Pilots are used The RCST will report a value that has been used for transmission to the RCST within the most recent 60 seconds. If this is not relevant, the RCST will report 'unknown'.

dvbRcsFwdStatusBer.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusBer
dvbRcsFwdStatusBer.description: Provides the RCST BER on the Forward Link in log10 units.

dvbRcsFwdStatusCnr.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusCnr
dvbRcsFwdStatusCnr.description: Provides the RCST CNR on the Forward Link in 0.1 dB units.

dvbRcsFwdStatusRxPower.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusRxPower
dvbRcsFwdStatusRxPower.description: Provides the power level of the forward link as received at the IDU, in 0.1 dBm units.

dvbRcsRtnConfigMaxEirp.name: dvbRcsRtnConfigMaxEirp
dvbRcsRtnConfigMaxEirp.description: Max Equivalent Isotropic Radiated Power (EIRP) of the RCST, given in resolution of 0.1 dBm and applied when the IDU can, itself, set the necessary IDU TX output level, e.g., when using a BUC that has a power level detector and that provides sufficient feedback to the IDU.

dvbRcsRtnConfigDefIfLevel.name: dvbRcsRtnConfigDefIfLevel
dvbRcsRtnConfigDefIfLevel.description: IDU TX output level applied in case the dvbRcsRtnConfigMaxEirp cannot be used. The resolution is 0.1 dBm and the accuracy is +/- 1 dBm.

dvbRcsRtnStatusEbN0.name: dvbRcsRtnStatusEbN0
dvbRcsRtnStatusEbN0.description: The EbN0 value reported for the return link, referenced to the regular SYNC burst transmission, in 0.1 dB units.

dvbRcsRtnStatusSFDuration.name: dvbRcsRtnStatusSFDuration
dvbRcsRtnStatusSFDuration.description: The duration of the currently applied return link superframe structure, in tenths of milliseconds.

dvbRcsRtnStatusPayloadUnit.name: dvbRcsRtnStatusPayloadUnit
dvbRcsRtnStatusPayloadUnit.description: Indicates if the payload unit used for the return link is ATM or MPEG.

dvbRcsRcstCompliance1.name: dvbRcsRcstCompliance1
dvbRcsRcstCompliance1.description: The compliance statement for DVB-RCS terminals that are compliant with SatLabs System Recommendations. Compliance is linked to the support by the terminal of the options or features defined in the SatLabs System Recommendations. The supported options and features of a terminal are declared in objects dvbRcsSystemSatLabsOptionsDeclaration and dvbRcsSystemSatLabsFeaturesDeclaration respectively.

dvbRcsRcstSystemGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstSystemGroup
dvbRcsRcstSystemGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information applicable for basic device management support.

dvbRcsRcstNetworkGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstNetworkGroup
dvbRcsRcstNetworkGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic networking management support.

dvbRcsRcstExtNetworkGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstExtNetworkGroup
dvbRcsRcstExtNetworkGroup.description: A collection of objects providing extended networking management support.

dvbRcsRcstDnsGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstDnsGroup
dvbRcsRcstDnsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing DNS management support.

dvbRcsRcstInstallGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstInstallGroup
dvbRcsRcstInstallGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information applicable for basic installation support.

dvbRcsRcstExtInstallGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstExtInstallGroup
dvbRcsRcstExtInstallGroup.description: A collection of objects providing extended device installation support.

dvbRcsRcstQosGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstQosGroup
dvbRcsRcstQosGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic access to QoS configuration data.

dvbRcsRcstEnhancedClassifierGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstEnhancedClassifierGroup
dvbRcsRcstEnhancedClassifierGroup.description: A collection of objects providing support for management of the enhanced classifier.

dvbRcsRcstMpegQosGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstMpegQosGroup
dvbRcsRcstMpegQosGroup.description: A collection of objects providing access to MPEG-related link QoS configuration data.

dvbRcsRcstGlobalQosGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstGlobalQosGroup
dvbRcsRcstGlobalQosGroup.description: A collection of objects providing access to global RCST QoS configuration data.

dvbRcsRcstStrictQosGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstStrictQosGroup
dvbRcsRcstStrictQosGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing management of strict channel ID dispatching.

dvbRcsRcstControlGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstControlGroup
dvbRcsRcstControlGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing basic RCST control.

dvbRcsRcstExtControlGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstExtControlGroup
dvbRcsRcstExtControlGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing extended RCST control.

dvbRcsRcstStateGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstStateGroup
dvbRcsRcstStateGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing access to RCST state.

dvbRcsFwdConfigGroup.name: dvbRcsFwdConfigGroup
dvbRcsFwdConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic start forward link configuration support.

dvbRcsFwdStatusGroup.name: dvbRcsFwdStatusGroup
dvbRcsFwdStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects providing forward link status.

dvbRcsRtnConfigGroup.name: dvbRcsRtnConfigGroup
dvbRcsRtnConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic return link configuration support.

dvbRcsRtnExtConfigGroup.name: dvbRcsRtnExtConfigGroup
dvbRcsRtnExtConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing extended return link configuration support.

dvbRcsRtnStatusGroup.name: dvbRcsRtnStatusGroup
dvbRcsRtnStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing access to return link status.

dvbRcsRtnExtStatusGroup.name: dvbRcsRtnExtStatusGroup
dvbRcsRtnExtStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects allowing access to extended return link status.

dvbRcsRcstOduListGroup.name: dvbRcsRcstOduListGroup
dvbRcsRcstOduListGroup.description: A collection of objects supporting flexible selection of ODU devices.
